ing (Plato). The repro can't achieve a readout playback of the original space - the space I experienced in 3-74 when I woke up upon recognizing my \"world\" as my own former memory fragments. Christ woke me up intentionally; this is what is meant by salvation. The knowledge (gnosis) of our situation; awakening is temporary but The knowledge (i.e. of our situation) is permanent have already writter about it prior to 3-74 because the tape is fed to me again + again This isn't the first time, which is why I remembered 3-74 in advance \"memory\" - simulated. Because it's fed to us again + again. Not just fed back once but forever (cf \"Tempunauts\"). It is - hell! + His decision is sua a Christ is emptying hell generis, it isn't merit on our part, although There is a justice to it in Ma'at's terms: a harmony + proportion, as in geometry. As they can't reproduce space properly here. like a power drain! t's used up as time This is the significance of, when I woke up, my experiencing vast spaces. + of they don't have stace right, then the whole simulation is faulty not an accurate analog of the actual reality it reproduces. This space of Beethoven's is the void of God himself. 485 as of 3-74 I have something to compare the simulation. (as written about in e.g. \"Joint\") with. the void of God - the space (volume) saw in 3-74 = the inner firmanent of Bruno. to enter this space is to be liberated the age of the spirit - from the simulation of recirculated memories. i always before when I've read over what I wrote when loaded I've found only nonsense. But this time: the insight that they haven't got space right shows this is a simulation - it's a fascinating possi‐ bility when linked to my previous insight about the strident radio indicating I was waking up. The reason that I find it fascinating is that it answers the Q: \"simulated in comparison to what? If, for example, you had never heard a live orchestra how could you detect 1) that a recording was in fact a recording + 2